        "title": "Head of Channel Management (Amazon)",
        "description": "<p>The head of channel management (Amazon) is driving marketplace and consumer insights, measurable results and fast-forward innovation to advocate the Miele brand identity and sales presence at Amazon. Main tasks include leading the development of growth strategies and reactive initiatives to drive top-line sales, customer acquisition and traffic through the Amazon vendor and Amazon advertising platforms – This role collaborates with Marketing and eCommerce-Teams across the complete global organization to accelerate the benefit of growth initiatives and optimization programs, and continuously reports insights, learnings and developments, thanks to deep analytical mindset and experience.</p>\n<p>YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES</p>\n<p>•Primary source of information for all stakeholders relating to analytics and performance marketing; act as a consultant to regional functions by providing guidance</p>\n<p>•Manage product ads on Amazon and potentially other marketplaces; Manage bids throughout entire campaign</p>\n<p>•Mentoring performance manager and manage cross-functional projects; drive the collection and understanding of customer engagement data</p>\n<p>•Manage the allocated performance marketing budget  for driving the consumer acquisition across all digital marketplace channels – in connection Miele X marketing</p>\n<p>•Optimize products to e-commerce marketplace channels</p>\n<p>•Lead the selection of tools to analyze performance and market data; monitor and track performance of all campaigns on all marketplace channels, including testing, reporting and performance dashboarding</p>\n<p>•Monitor reviews and track customer feedback</p>\n<p>•Quarterly definition and review of success metrics based on the overall market trends, main competitors etc.</p>\n<p>YOUR PROFILE</p>\n<p>•Ideally university degree in business studies, major in marketing / digital brand management and other relevant fields</p>\n<p>•Foundational experience working for a premium brand  in consumer or FMCG industry with deep market and (premium) consumer behavior knowledge</p>\n<p>•Minimum 3 years experience managing either Amazon FBA, Seller Central or Vendor Central accounts ​\n•Acknowledged communicator at all levels with a hands-on attitude with experience in managing international, cross-functional team and agile ways of working​</p>\n<p>•Ability to draw conclusions based on analytic reports and KPIs; in-depth skills in managing large scale, complex paid search and shopping feed campaigns; strong math and analytical skills; extremely proficient in Microsoft Excel​</p>\n<p>•Excellent presentation skills and ability to construct a cohesive, visual story to (non-) technical audiences; fluent business English, additional languages are an advantage​</p>\n<p>•Deep Consumer Centricity Mindset and ability to change perspectives​</p>\n",
        "how_to_apply": "<p>We are looking for your application. You can apply here:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.miele-x.com/jobs/head-of-channel-management-amazon/?utm_source=GitHub%20jobs&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=EN_MX_062020\">https://www.miele-x.com/jobs/head-of-channel-management-amazon/?utm_source=GitHub%20jobs&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=EN_MX_062020</a></p>\n",
